  "solution": {
    "format": "pdf-layout-text",
    "rawText": "We first expand the brackets to obtain\n                            Z 16                Z 16\n                                 1                   1\n                                   + 2 + x dx −        − 2 + x dx.\n                             9   x               9   x\n\nSince these integrals have the same limits, we can combine them into a single integral to get\n               Z 16 \u0012          \u0013 \u0012             \u0013 Z 16\n                      1              1\n                        +2+x −         −2+x =          4 dx = 4 × (16 − 9) = 28,\n                9     x              x               9\n\nwhich is option F.\n\nNote that integration of x1 is not on the specification for this test; it is, of course, possible to\nanswer this question by calculating both integrals explicitly and then subtracting, but it is much\nmore work than the solution just presented.\n\n\n\n\nVersion 1.0, September 2023                                                                  Page 4"
  },
